text.section:
The mayor is authorized to supervise, administer, and control all departments and agencies as may be created by KRS 67C.101 to 67C.137 or created by ordinance. The mayor shall appoint all department and agency directors. The appointees shall serve at the pleasure of the mayor. Specifically, the mayor shall:
Prepare and submit an annual report coinciding with the fiscal year, on the state of the consolidated local government, to be presented at a public meeting of the council;
Submit an annual budget;
Oversee the administration and implementation of the adopted budget ordinance;
Enforce the ordinances of the consolidated local government;
Supervise all officers, agents, employees, cabinets, departments, offices, agencies, functions, and duties of the consolidated local government;
Call special meetings of the consolidated local government council;
Appoint and remove his or her own staff at his or her own pleasure;
Execute written contracts or obligations of the consolidated local government; and
Approve or veto ordinances and resolutions adopted by the consolidated local government council.
